  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales Merchandiser",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Title: Sales Merchandiser (FMCG)</strong></p><p>We are looking for a proactive and detail-oriented Sales Merchandiser to join our growing team at Ouji (Singapore) Pte Ltd. This role is responsible for ensuring excellent product visibility, optimal stock levels, and effective in-store execution across assigned retail outlets. The successful candidate will work closely with the sales and operations teams to drive sell-out performance and brand presence.<br /></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Visit assigned retail outlets to ensure shelves are well-stocked, properly displayed, and merchandised according to company guidelines</p></li><li><p>Execute in-store merchandising, planograms, promotions, and point-of-sale displays</p></li><li><p>Monitor stock levels, expiry dates, and replenishment needs to prevent out-of-stock situations</p></li><li><p>Build and maintain good relationships with store personnel and supervisors</p></li><li><p>Collect and report market intelligence, competitor activities, pricing, and promotions</p></li><li><p>Support sales activities, product launches, and promotional campaigns</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with internal teams on stock issues, display setups, and operational matters</p></li><li><p>Submit timely reports, photos, and updates on merchandising activities<br /></p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>At least 1 year of merchandising or FMCG retail experience preferred</p></li><li><p>Fresh candidates with strong interest in FMCG merchandising are welcome to apply</p></li><li><p>Must be able to lift heavy objects and be comfortable with field-based work.</p></li><li><p>Good communication and interpersonal skills</p></li><li><p>Detail-oriented, responsible, and able to work independently<br /></p></li></ul><p><strong>Working Schedule:</strong></p><p>Working days: Wednesday to Monday</p><p>Rest day: Tuesday</p>",
